cs.ET, cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses a new memory structure based on RRAM technology, which is an emerging technology in the field of memory devices. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on implementing neural networks using RRAM-based in-memory computing, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes a new memory structure and associated sense circuitry, which can be considered as a hardware architecture design. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper evaluates the proposed approach for image recognition applications, which is a sub-field of computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems): The paper discusses the energy efficiency of the proposed approach, which is a key aspect of embedded systems design.
